T1  - Interfirm Competition for Human Resources: Evidence From the Software Industry
AU  - Gardner, Timothy M.
Y1  - 2005/04/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2005.16928398
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2005.16928398
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 237
EP  - 256
VL  - 48
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - To test a model of interfirm competition for human resources, firms' responses to the loss of employees to single rivals were examined. Results suggest that attributes of hiring firms and of hired employees are associated with target firms' decisions to defend and retaliate against labor market rivals. The findings have implications for the validation of intrafirm differences in human resource systems. This study opens the door for further theorizing and modeling of interfirm competition for intangible resources.
AB  - To test a model of interfirm competition for human resources, firms' responses to the loss of employees to single rivals were examined. Results suggest that attributes of hiring firms and of hired employees are associated with target firms' decisions to defend and retaliate against labor market rivals. The findings have implications for the validation of intrafirm differences in human resource systems. This study opens the door for further theorizing and modeling of interfirm competition for intangible resources.
